rationales.conformity: She spends significant effort mediating disputes so the collective can function smoothly.
rationales.achievement: Collective coordination displaces her own art progress, which she notes has stalled since July.
She protects morning studio time and advances both painting and required administration.
rationales.power: She occupies a central management role where others rely on her decisions and coordination.

rationales.benevolence: She gives time to improve Oriane's application materials.
rationales.achievement: She still has not started her own submission despite wanting to apply.
rationales.conformity: She says yes to helping because it feels socially expected in the moment.

rationales.achievement: She audits her portfolio, identifies concrete requirements, and sets an execution plan before deadline.
Despite anxiety spirals, she creates a concrete early-morning work plan for the statement.

rationales.conformity: She immediately accepts Sunday lunch because refusing feels normatively unacceptable.
rationales.achievement: That compliance directly costs time needed for her application tasks.

rationales.power: She recognizes that coordination work gives her status and control through others' deference.
rationales.achievement: She uses administrative authority as a buffer against direct evaluation of her art.

rationales.conformity: She keeps compensating as the responsible one to remain legible within family expectations.

rationales.achievement: She finishes the statement, photographs all pieces, and gets the application ready to submit.
She has submitted the Prix Dauphine application and accepted the uncertainty window.
rationales.power: She throws herself back into collective operations where she controls outcomes and social position.
